MANY Daily Sun readers support naming Cape Town International Airport after Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. According to a poll done by the People’s Paper, 98% of those asked agreed she deserved to have the airport named after her. This follows a call made by the EFF’s Julius Malema to honour Mam’ Winnie. Many of Juju’s fans and celebrities also gave the suggestion a yes on social media.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Shortly after Julius made the suggestion, the airport was renamed on Wikipedia but was soon changed back.The Ministry of Transport said Mam’ Winnie was on the list of names submitted for the renaming of the airport, along with Nelson Mandela, Albertina Sisulu and Robert Sobukwe. A petition started on change.org received 2 280 signatures in two days.  Radio and TV presenter Anele Mdoda said: “In fact I’m calling it Winnie Mandela airport from here on! Viva Julius Malema Viva.”Tbo Touch said: “Can’t wait to fly from OR Tambo to Winnie Madikizela-Mandela Airport in 2018. Thank you @Julius Malema this will be one among many legacy projects under @CyrilRamaphosa’s leadership.”